Baltika of Estonia Second-Quarter Loss Narrows on Lower Costs

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-07-25T11:18:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/baltika-of-estonia-second-quarter-loss-narrows-on-lower-costs.html
AS Baltika, the third-largest listed
Baltic clothing company, said its second-quarter loss narrowed
after a store closing in  Russia  cut distribution costs.  The net loss declined to 444,000 euros ($638,000) from
883,000 euros a year earlier, the Tallinn-based company said in
a regulatory statement today. Revenue was little changed at 12.6
million euros.  Distribution costs fell 8 percent from a year earlier
mainly due to the closing of the Europeysky store in Moscow at
the start of April, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  